///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @file LUT.dox
 * @brief Documentation for the LUT (Lookup Table) module in MIDILAR.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @addtogroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 *
 * This module provides the foundation for fast, flexible signal shaping using precomputed lookup tables.
 * It includes dimensional LUT types as well as specialized LUT generators under the `Periodic` and `Shaping` namespaces.
 *
 * ### Topics:
 * - @ref MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_1D
 * - @ref MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_2D
 * - @ref MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_3D
 * - @ref MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_Periodic
 * - @ref MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_Shaping
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_1D LUT1D
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 * @brief One-dimensional lookup tables with fast index access and linear interpolation.
 *
 * The base class `BaseLUT` provides the core interface for single-variable LUTs used in shaping curves and waveforms.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_2D LUT2D
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 * @brief Two-dimensional lookup tables for morphing or parameter-dependent shaping.
 *
 * The `BaseLUT2D` class enables dynamic response curves based on two inputs, such as velocity vs morph.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_3D LUT3D
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 * @brief Three-dimensional lookup tables for complex control surfaces and real-time modulation.
 *
 * The `BaseLUT3D` class allows interpolation across three input axes, enabling expressive signal shaping with embedded performance in mind.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_Periodic Periodic LUT Generators
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 * @brief Predefined periodic waveforms: sine, triangle, square, saw, etc.
 *
 * These generators produce harmonically rich or smooth waveforms using LUTs optimized for phase continuity and alias-free playback.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT_Shaping Shaping LUT Generators
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_LUT
 * @brief Nonlinear transformation generators: log-exp, sigmoid, and velocity curves.
 *
 * Useful for expressive dynamic control and real-time parameter mapping based on user input or MIDI data.
 */
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
